{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TJwqQezvfibTRDiU7wWxgN","type":"tool_result","content":"315-}\n316-```\n317-\n318:**Coverage deduplication:** The verify task receives test results via output contract. The evaluator checks the contract's `testResults` field instead of re-running coverage. If `testResults.coverage >= target`, coverage is already met — no re-run.\n319-\n320-**Rationale:** The engine has all the data it needs from the output contract. Setting flags in the engine is deterministic and reliable — no dependency on the evaluator's ability to set flags in a subagent context.\n321-"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_016tHrCUqdH9scyVU8wnefbD","session_id":"b6bb3bfc-8778-4f16-a616-88028acc2431","uuid":"a0a5e7ee-309e-4048-8a1a-da7989b090b8","timestamp":"2026-04-03T18:26:41.223Z"}
