{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012QiF66fN9sSS3XMkAaEQyE","type":"tool_result","content":"113\t\n114\t## Epic 16: Hierarchical Flow Model & Engine-Handled Tasks\n115\t\n116\tUsers can define hierarchical workflows with engine-handled zero-token tasks, verify flag propagation, and telemetry collection.\n117\t\n118\t### Story 16.1: Hierarchical Flow Schema & Parser\n119\t\n120\tAs a user,\n121\tI want to define `execution`, `story_flow`, and `epic_flow` sections in workflow YAML,\n122\tSo that I can configure sprint-level, epic-level, and story-level behavior separately.\n123\t\n124\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n125\t\n126\t**Given** `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json`\n127\t**When** updated with `execution`, `story_flow`, and `epic_flow` sections\n128\t**Then** `execution` supports `max_parallel`, `isolation`, `merge_strategy`, `epic_strategy`, `story_strategy`\n129\t**And** `story_flow` accepts the same format as existing `flow` (task refs + loop blocks)\n130\t**And** `epic_flow` accepts task refs including built-in names `merge` and `validate`\n131\t**And** existing workflows with only `flow:` parse successfully (backward compat — treated as `story_flow`)\n132\t**And** `workflow-parser.ts` resolves hierarchical flow via `hierarchical-flow.ts`\n133\t**And** validation rejects `story_flow` tasks not defined in `tasks:` section\n134\t\n135\t### Story 16.2: Engine-Handled Null Tasks\n136\t\n137\tAs a developer,\n138\tI want tasks with `agent: null` to execute directly in the engine without LLM dispatch,\n139\tSo that telemetry collection and state bookkeeping cost zero tokens.\n140\t\n141\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n142\t\n143\t**Given** a task definition with `agent: null` in workflow YAML\n144\t**When** the workflow engine reaches this task in the flow\n145\t**Then** the engine looks up the task name in the null task handler registry\n146\t**And** calls the handler directly (no driver dispatch, no stream events)\n147\t**And** the handler receives `TaskContext` with story key, cost, duration, output contract\n148\t**And** unknown null task names produce a descriptive error\n149\t**And** null tasks complete in <10ms for data collection operations\n150\t\n151\t### Story 16.3: Telemetry Writer\n152\t\n153\tAs a developer,\n154\tI want structured telemetry written as NDJSON after each story completes,\n155\tSo that epic retros have rich data without per-session LLM cost.\n156\t\n157\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n158\t\n159\t**Given** a new `src/lib/telemetry-writer.ts`\n160\t**When** the `telemetry` null task handler runs after a story\n161\t**Then** it writes one NDJSON line to `.codeharness/telemetry.jsonl`\n162\t**And** each entry includes: version, timestamp, storyKey, epicId, duration_ms, cost_usd, attempts, acResults, filesChanged, testResults, errors\n163\t**And** fields not available are set to `null` (never fabricated)\n164\t**And** writes are append-only with `appendFileSync`\n165\t**And** telemetry entries include `version: 1` for forward compatibility\n166\t**And** a `readTelemetryForEpic(epicId)` function returns all entries for a given epic\n167\t\n168\t### Story 16.4: Verify Flag Propagation\n169\t\n170\tAs a developer,\n171\tI want the engine to set `tests_passed` and `coverage_met` from the dev task's output contract,\n172\tSo that verification doesn't fail on missing flags set by subagents.\n173\t\n174\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n175\t\n176\t**Given** the implement task completes with an output contract containing `testResults`\n177\t**When** `testResults.failed === 0`\n178\t**Then** the engine sets `tests_passed = true` in the state file\n179\t**And** when `testResults.coverage >= coverage.target`\n180\t**Then** the engine sets `coverage_met = true` in the state file\n181\t**And** the verify task no longer needs to set these flags itself\n182\t**And** existing behavior is preserved when output contract has no testResults\n183\t\n184\t### Story 16.5: Coverage Deduplication\n185\t\n186\tAs a developer,\n187\tI want the verify phase to read coverage from the output contract instead of re-running,\n188\tSo that coverage is not computed twice per story.\n189\t\n190\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n191\t\n192\t**Given** the implement task's output contract contains `testResults.coverage`\n193\t**When** the verify task starts\n194\t**Then** if `coverage_met` is already true (set by engine in 16.4), skip coverage re-run\n195\t**And** the evaluator prompt includes coverage result from the contract as context\n196\t**And** if no coverage data exists in the contract, verify runs coverage normally (fallback)\n197\t\n198\t### Story 16.6: Story Flow Execution\n199\t\n200\tAs a developer,\n201\tI want the workflow engine to execute `story_flow` for each story within an epic,\n202\tSo that the hierarchical flow model drives story-level execution.\n203\t\n204\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n205\t\n206\t**Given** a workflow with `story_flow: [implement, verify, loop: [retry, verify], telemetry]`\n207\t**When** the engine processes an epic's stories\n208\t**Then** each story runs through the complete story_flow pipeline\n209\t**And** the `telemetry` null task runs after verify completes (or after loop exits)\n210\t**And** story_flow respects existing loop semantics (max iterations, circuit breaker)\n211\t**And** backward compat: workflows with `flow:` (no `story_flow`) produce identical behavior\n212\t\n213\t## Epic 17: Worktree Management & Lane Pool\n214\t\n215\tUsers can run epics in parallel using git worktree isolation with configurable concurrency.\n216\t\n217\t### Story 17.1: Worktree Manager\n218\t\n219\tAs a developer,\n220\tI want a worktree manager that handles git worktree create/merge/cleanup,\n221\tSo that parallel epics run in isolated working directories.\n222\t\n223\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n224\t\n225\t**Given** a new `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts`\n226\t**When** `createWorktree(epicId, slug)` is called\n227\t**Then** it creates branch `codeharness/epic-{N}-{slug}` from main\n228\t**And** creates worktree at `/tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-{N}`\n229\t**And** returns the worktree path\n230\t**And** creation completes within 10 seconds (NFR1)\n231\t**And** `cleanupWorktree(epicId)` removes worktree and deletes branch\n232\t**And** `listWorktrees()` returns all active codeharness worktrees"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_016tHrCUqdH9scyVU8wnefbD","session_id":"b6bb3bfc-8778-4f16-a616-88028acc2431","uuid":"1a4871b4-2a10-466c-bd65-96c5dcdd9838","timestamp":"2026-04-03T18:26:49.614Z"}
