{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016D4AgJVAiPk9EUYLSmsB6i","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 16.5: Coverage Deduplication\n2\t\n3\tStatus: ready-for-dev\n4\t\n5\t## Story\n6\t\n7\tAs a developer,\n8\tI want the verify phase to read coverage from the output contract instead of re-running,\n9\tso that coverage is not computed twice per story.\n10\t\n11\t## Acceptance Criteria\n12\t\n13\t1. **Given** the implement task's output contract contains `testResults.coverage` and `coverage_met` is already `true` in the harness state (set by engine flag propagation in 16-4), **when** the verify task starts, **then** the evaluator prompt includes the coverage result from the contract as context (e.g., \"Coverage already met: 95% (target: 90%)\"). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n14\t\n15\t2. **Given** `coverage_met` is `true` in the harness state, **when** the verify/evaluator runs, **then** the coverage tool (`runCoverage`/`checkOnlyCoverage`) is NOT invoked — the evaluator receives the pre-computed coverage data instead. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n16\t\n17\t3. **Given** the implement task's output contract has `testResults: null` (no coverage data), **when** the verify task starts, **then** coverage runs normally via the existing path (`runCoverage` or `checkOnlyCoverage`), as a fallback. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n18\t\n19\t4. **Given** the implement task's output contract has `testResults.coverage` but `coverage_met` is `false` (coverage below target), **when** the verify task starts, **then** coverage runs normally — deduplication only applies when coverage is already met. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t5. **Given** `coverage_met` is `true` and `tests_passed` is `true`, **when** `checkPreconditions()` runs in the verify orchestrator, **then** preconditions pass without triggering any coverage computation. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n22\t\n23\t6. **Given** the evaluator prompt includes contract coverage context, **when** the evaluator inspects coverage, **then** it can determine coverage status from the prompt context alone without running external commands. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n26\t\n27\t- [ ] Task 1: Add coverage deduplication to the evaluator prompt builder (AC: #1, #6)\n28\t  - [ ] Modify `buildEvaluatorPrompt()` in `src/lib/evaluator.ts` (or the workflow engine's evaluator dispatch path) to accept optional coverage context\n29\t  - [ ] When `coverage_met === true` in harness state and `testResults.coverage` exists in the output contract, append a coverage context block to the evaluator prompt\n30\t  - [ ] Format: \"Coverage already verified by engine: {coverage}% (target: {target}%). No re-run needed.\"\n31\t  - [ ] When no contract coverage data or `coverage_met === false`, do not append — evaluator uses normal flow\n32\t\n33\t- [ ] Task 2: Add coverage skip logic to the coverage command/runner path (AC: #2, #3, #4)\n34\t  - [ ] In `src/commands/coverage.ts` or the coverage evaluation entry point, check harness state for `coverage_met === true` before running `runCoverage()`\n35\t  - [ ] If `coverage_met` is already true, return a synthetic `CoverageResult` with data from the output contract (or simply skip the run and log the skip)\n36\t  - [ ] If `coverage_met` is false or state is unavailable, fall through to existing `runCoverage()` path\n37\t  - [ ] Ensure `checkOnlyCoverage()` respects the same skip logic\n38\t\n39\t- [ ] Task 3: Wire output contract data through the verify dispatch path (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4)\n40\t  - [ ] The workflow engine already passes `previousOutputContract` to task dispatches via `buildPromptWithContractContext()` — verify that the verify task receives the implement task's output contract\n41\t  - [ ] If the verify task does NOT currently receive the output contract, wire it through\n42\t  - [ ] Extract `testResults.coverage` from the contract for use in deduplication decisions\n43\t\n44\t- [ ] Task 4: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#6)\n45\t  - [ ] Test: evaluator prompt includes coverage context when `coverage_met === true` and contract has coverage\n46\t  - [ ] Test: evaluator prompt does NOT include coverage context when `coverage_met === false`\n47\t  - [ ] Test: evaluator prompt does NOT include coverage context when contract has `testResults: null`\n48\t  - [ ] Test: `runCoverage` is not called when `coverage_met === true`\n49\t  - [ ] Test: `runCoverage` IS called when `coverage_met === false` (fallback)\n50\t  - [ ] Test: `checkPreconditions()` passes when both flags are true (existing test, verify still works)\n51\t\n52\t- [ ] Task 5: Verify backward compatibility (AC: #3, #4)\n53\t  - [ ] Confirm that workflows without output contracts (older workflows) still run coverage normally\n54\t  - [ ] Confirm the `codeharness coverage` CLI command works unchanged (it doesn't go through engine flag propagation)\n55\t\n56\t## Dev Notes\n57\t\n58\t### Architecture Constraints\n59\t\n60\t- **Architecture Decision 7** (architecture-parallel-execution.md) specifies: \"The verify task receives test results via output contract. The evaluator checks the contract's `testResults` field instead of re-running coverage. If `testResults.coverage >= target`, coverage is already met — no re-run.\"\n61\t- The engine already sets `coverage_met` and `tests_passed` in story 16-4 via `propagateVerifyFlags()` in `workflow-engine.ts`.\n62\t- The evaluator prompt is built in `src/lib/evaluator.ts` via `buildEvaluatorPrompt()`. Currently it's a static string — it needs to accept coverage context.\n63\t- The workflow engine passes output contracts between tasks via `buildPromptWithContractContext()` in `src/lib/agents/output-contract.ts`.\n64\t\n65\t### Key Files to Modify\n66\t\n67\t| File | Change |\n68\t|------|--------|\n69\t| `src/lib/evaluator.ts` | Extend `buildEvaluatorPrompt()` to accept and include coverage context |\n70\t| `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` | Pass coverage state info to evaluator dispatch path |\n71\t| `src/commands/coverage.ts` | Add skip logic when `coverage_met === true` (optional — depends on whether the CLI command or the engine drives coverage during verify) |\n72\t| `src/lib/coverage/evaluator.ts` | Possibly add a `skipIfMet()` check before `evaluateCoverage()` |\n73\t\n74\t### Key Files to Read (Do Not Modify)\n75\t\n76\t| File | Why |\n77\t|------|-----|\n78\t| `src/modules/verify/orchestrator.ts` | `checkPreconditions()` reads `tests_passed` and `coverage_met` from state — this is the gate |\n79\t| `src/lib/agents/types.ts` | `OutputContract` and `TestResults` interfaces — `testResults.coverage` is `number \\| null` |\n80\t| `src/lib/agents/output-contract.ts` | `buildPromptWithContractContext()` — how output contracts flow between tasks |\n81\t| `src/lib/coverage/runner.ts` | `runCoverage()` and `checkOnlyCoverage()` — what gets skipped |\n82\t\n83\t### Architecture Decision Reference\n84\t\n85\tFrom `architecture-parallel-execution.md`, Decision 7:\n86\t\n87\t```typescript\n88\t// After implement task completes:\n89\tif (taskName === 'implement' && outputContract?.testResults) {\n90\t  const { passed, failed, coverage } = outputContract.testResults;\n91\t  if (failed === 0) await setState('tests_passed', true);\n92\t  if (coverage >= state.coverage.target) await setState('coverage_met', true);\n93\t}\n94\t```\n95\t\n96\tCoverage deduplication: The verify task receives test results via output contract. The evaluator checks the contract's `testResults` field instead of re-running coverage. If `testResults.coverage >= target`, coverage is already met — no re-run.\n97\t\n98\t### Current Coverage Flow (Before This Story)\n99\t\n100\t1. Implement task runs, produces output contract with `testResults`\n101\t2. Engine sets `tests_passed` and `coverage_met` flags (story 16-4)\n102\t3. Verify task starts, `checkPreconditions()` reads flags — passes if both true\n103\t4. **But:** the evaluator still calls `runCoverage()` to compute coverage independently, duplicating work\n104\t5. `updateCoverageState()` writes the same flags again\n105\t\n106\t### Target Coverage Flow (After This Story)\n107\t\n108\t1. Implement task runs, produces output contract with `testResults`\n109\t2. Engine sets `tests_passed` and `coverage_met` flags (story 16-4)\n110\t3. Verify task starts, `checkPreconditions()` reads flags — passes\n111\t4. **New:** Engine detects `coverage_met === true`, includes coverage data in evaluator prompt\n112\t5. **New:** Coverage tool is NOT re-run — evaluator uses contract data\n113\t6. Evaluator evaluates ACs using coverage context from prompt\n114\t\n115\t### Edge Cases\n116\t\n117\t- **`testResults.coverage` is `null`:** Fallback to normal coverage run. `coverage_met` will be `false` (null >= N is false), so dedup won't trigger.\n118\t- **`coverage_met` set by engine but evaluator re-runs coverage anyway:** This should be prevented by the skip logic. If the evaluator independently decides to run `npx vitest --coverage`, that's outside our control — the skip only applies to the programmatic path.\n119\t- **CLI `codeharness coverage` command:** This is user-initiated and should always run coverage. The dedup skip only applies to the engine-driven verify flow.\n120\t\n121\t### Project Structure Notes\n122\t\n123\t- Source: TypeScript in `src/`, compiled to `dist/`\n124\t- Tests: vitest, colocated in `__tests__/` directories\n125\t- ESM modules — use `.js` extensions in imports\n126\t- Build: `npm run build` (TypeScript compilation)\n127\t- Test: `npm test` (vitest)\n128\t\n129\t### References\n130\t\n131\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-parallel-execution.md#Story 16.5]\n132\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Decision 7 — Verify Flag Propagation]\n133\t- [Source: src/lib/evaluator.ts — buildEvaluatorPrompt(), runBlindEvaluator()]\n134\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-engine.ts — propagateVerifyFlags(), dispatchTaskWithResult()]\n135\t- [Source: src/modules/verify/orchestrator.ts — checkPreconditions()]\n136\t- [Source: src/lib/coverage/evaluator.ts — evaluateCoverage(), updateCoverageState()]\n137\t- [Source: src/lib/coverage/runner.ts — runCoverage(), checkOnlyCoverage()]\n138\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/types.ts — OutputContract, TestResults interfaces]\n139\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/output-contract.ts — buildPromptWithContractContext()]\n140\t\n141\t### Previous Story (16-4) Intelligence\n142\t\n143\t- Flag propagation implemented in `workflow-engine.ts` via `propagateVerifyFlags()` — called after every `dispatchTaskWithResult()` return.\n144\t- Guards on `taskName === 'implement'` and `contract?.testResults` being non-null.\n145\t- Reads harness state via `readStateWithBody()`, sets `session_flags.tests_passed` and `session_flags.coverage_met`, writes back.\n146\t- 8 unit tests added. All 4747 tests pass.\n147\t- `checkPreconditions()` in verify orchestrator already reads these exact flags — no changes needed to preconditions.\n148\t- Code review caught: duplicate type definitions, missing `projectDir` parameter, misleading JSDoc. Be precise.\n149\t- Currently `outputContract.testResults` is always `null` (hardcoded in engine). Flag propagation will activate when engine gains test result parsing from agent output.\n150\t\n151\t### Git Intelligence\n152\t\n153\tRecent commits:\n154\t- `21e441c feat: story 16-4 — verify flag propagation`\n155\t- `1831a88 feat: story 16-3 — telemetry writer module`\n156\t- `07e94a2 feat: story 16-2 — engine-handled null tasks`\n157\t- `e3c4761 feat: story 16-1 — hierarchical flow schema & parser`\n158\t- Commit pattern: `feat: story {N}-{M} — {title}`\n159\t\n160\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n161\t## Verification Requirements\n162\t\n163\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/16-5-coverage-deduplication-proof.md)\n164\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n165\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n166\t\n167\t## Documentation Requirements\n168\t\n169\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n170\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/16-5-coverage-deduplication.md\n171\t\n172\t## Testing Requirements\n173\t\n174\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n175\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n176\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n177\t\n178\t## Dev Agent Record\n179\t\n180\t### Agent Model Used\n181\t\n182\t{{agent_model_name_version}}\n183\t\n184\t### Debug Log References\n185\t\n186\t### Completion Notes List\n187\t\n188\t### File List\n189\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b6bb3bfc-8778-4f16-a616-88028acc2431","uuid":"098df1d4-0898-4602-9aa8-fbbf7eadf77d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T18:30:24.754Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-5-coverage-deduplication.md","content":"# Story 16.5: Coverage Deduplication\n\nStatus: ready-for-dev\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer,\nI want the verify phase to read coverage from the output contract instead of re-running,\nso that coverage is not computed twice per story.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. **Given** the implement task's output contract contains `testResults.coverage` and `coverage_met` is already `true` in the harness state (set by engine flag propagation in 16-4), **when** the verify task starts, **then** the evaluator prompt includes the coverage result from the contract as context (e.g., \"Coverage already met: 95% (target: 90%)\"). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n2. **Given** `coverage_met` is `true` in the harness state, **when** the verify/evaluator runs, **then** the coverage tool (`runCoverage`/`checkOnlyCoverage`) is NOT invoked — the evaluator receives the pre-computed coverage data instead. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n3. **Given** the implement task's output contract has `testResults: null` (no coverage data), **when** the verify task starts, **then** coverage runs normally via the existing path (`runCoverage` or `checkOnlyCoverage`), as a fallback. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n4. **Given** the implement task's output contract has `testResults.coverage` but `coverage_met` is `false` (coverage below target), **when** the verify task starts, **then** coverage runs normally — deduplication only applies when coverage is already met. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n5. **Given** `coverage_met` is `true` and `tests_passed` is `true`, **when** `checkPreconditions()` runs in the verify orchestrator, **then** preconditions pass without triggering any coverage computation. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n6. **Given** the evaluator prompt includes contract coverage context, **when** the evaluator inspects coverage, **then** it can determine coverage status from the prompt context alone without running external commands. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n## Tasks / Subtasks\n\n- [ ] Task 1: Add coverage deduplication to the evaluator prompt builder (AC: #1, #6)\n  - [ ] Modify `buildEvaluatorPrompt()` in `src/lib/evaluator.ts` (or the workflow engine's evaluator dispatch path) to accept optional coverage context\n  - [ ] When `coverage_met === true` in harness state and `testResults.coverage` exists in the output contract, append a coverage context block to the evaluator prompt\n  - [ ] Format: \"Coverage already verified by engine: {coverage}% (target: {target}%). No re-run needed.\"\n  - [ ] When no contract coverage data or `coverage_met === false`, do not append — evaluator uses normal flow\n\n- [ ] Task 2: Add coverage skip logic to the coverage command/runner path (AC: #2, #3, #4)\n  - [ ] In `src/commands/coverage.ts` or the coverage evaluation entry point, check harness state for `coverage_met === true` before running `runCoverage()`\n  - [ ] If `coverage_met` is already true, return a synthetic `CoverageResult` with data from the output contract (or simply skip the run and log the skip)\n  - [ ] If `coverage_met` is false or state is unavailable, fall through to existing `runCoverage()` path\n  - [ ] Ensure `checkOnlyCoverage()` respects the same skip logic\n\n- [ ] Task 3: Wire output contract data through the verify dispatch path (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4)\n  - [ ] The workflow engine already passes `previousOutputContract` to task dispatches via `buildPromptWithContractContext()` — verify that the verify task receives the implement task's output contract\n  - [ ] If the verify task does NOT currently receive the output contract, wire it through\n  - [ ] Extract `testResults.coverage` from the contract for use in deduplication decisions\n\n- [ ] Task 4: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#6)\n  - [ ] Test: evaluator prompt includes coverage context when `coverage_met === true` and contract has coverage\n  - [ ] Test: evaluator prompt does NOT include coverage context when `coverage_met === false`\n  - [ ] Test: evaluator prompt does NOT include coverage context when contract has `testResults: null`\n  - [ ] Test: `runCoverage` is not called when `coverage_met === true`\n  - [ ] Test: `runCoverage` IS called when `coverage_met === false` (fallback)\n  - [ ] Test: `checkPreconditions()` passes when both flags are true (existing test, verify still works)\n\n- [ ] Task 5: Verify backward compatibility (AC: #3, #4)\n  - [ ] Confirm that workflows without output contracts (older workflows) still run coverage normally\n  - [ ] Confirm the `codeharness coverage` CLI command works unchanged (it doesn't go through engine flag propagation)\n\n## Dev Notes\n\n### Architecture Constraints\n\n- **Architecture Decision 7** (architecture-parallel-execution.md) specifies: \"The verify task receives test results via output contract. The evaluator checks the contract's `testResults` field instead of re-running coverage. If `testResults.coverage >= target`, coverage is already met — no re-run.\"\n- The engine already sets `coverage_met` and `tests_passed` in story 16-4 via `propagateVerifyFlags()` in `workflow-engine.ts`.\n- The evaluator prompt is built in `src/lib/evaluator.ts` via `buildEvaluatorPrompt()`. Currently it's a static string — it needs to accept coverage context.\n- The workflow engine passes output contracts between tasks via `buildPromptWithContractContext()` in `src/lib/agents/output-contract.ts`.\n\n### Key Files to Modify\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `src/lib/evaluator.ts` | Extend `buildEvaluatorPrompt()` to accept and include coverage context |\n| `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` | Pass coverage state info to evaluator dispatch path |\n| `src/commands/coverage.ts` | Add skip logic when `coverage_met === true` (optional — depends on whether the CLI command or the engine drives coverage during verify) |\n| `src/lib/coverage/evaluator.ts` | Possibly add a `skipIfMet()` check before `evaluateCoverage()` |\n\n### Key Files to Read (Do Not Modify)\n\n| File | Why |\n|------|-----|\n| `src/modules/verify/orchestrator.ts` | `checkPreconditions()` reads `tests_passed` and `coverage_met` from state — this is the gate |\n| `src/lib/agents/types.ts` | `OutputContract` and `TestResults` interfaces — `testResults.coverage` is `number \\| null` |\n| `src/lib/agents/output-contract.ts` | `buildPromptWithContractContext()` — how output contracts flow between tasks |\n| `src/lib/coverage/runner.ts` | `runCoverage()` and `checkOnlyCoverage()` — what gets skipped |\n\n### Architecture Decision Reference\n\nFrom `architecture-parallel-execution.md`, Decision 7:\n\n```typescript\n// After implement task completes:\nif (taskName === 'implement' && outputContract?.testResults) {\n  const { passed, failed, coverage } = outputContract.testResults;\n  if (failed === 0) await setState('tests_passed', true);\n  if (coverage >= state.coverage.target) await setState('coverage_met', true);\n}\n```\n\nCoverage deduplication: The verify task receives test results via output contract. The evaluator checks the contract's `testResults` field instead of re-running coverage. If `testResults.coverage >= target`, coverage is already met — no re-run.\n\n### Current Coverage Flow (Before This Story)\n\n1. Implement task runs, produces output contract with `testResults`\n2. Engine sets `tests_passed` and `coverage_met` flags (story 16-4)\n3. Verify task starts, `checkPreconditions()` reads flags — passes if both true\n4. **But:** the evaluator still calls `runCoverage()` to compute coverage independently, duplicating work\n5. `updateCoverageState()` writes the same flags again\n\n### Target Coverage Flow (After This Story)\n\n1. Implement task runs, produces output contract with `testResults`\n2. Engine sets `tests_passed` and `coverage_met` flags (story 16-4)\n3. Verify task starts, `checkPreconditions()` reads flags — passes\n4. **New:** Engine detects `coverage_met === true`, includes coverage data in evaluator prompt\n5. **New:** Coverage tool is NOT re-run — evaluator uses contract data\n6. Evaluator evaluates ACs using coverage context from prompt\n\n### Edge Cases\n\n- **`testResults.coverage` is `null`:** Fallback to normal coverage run. `coverage_met` will be `false` (null >= N is false), so dedup won't trigger.\n- **`coverage_met` set by engine but evaluator re-runs coverage anyway:** This should be prevented by the skip logic. If the evaluator independently decides to run `npx vitest --coverage`, that's outside our control — the skip only applies to the programmatic path.\n- **CLI `codeharness coverage` command:** This is user-initiated and should always run coverage. The dedup skip only applies to the engine-driven verify flow.\n\n### Project Structure Notes\n\n- Source: TypeScript in `src/`, compiled to `dist/`\n- Tests: vitest, colocated in `__tests__/` directories\n- ESM modules — use `.js` extensions in imports\n- Build: `npm run build` (TypeScript compilation)\n- Test: `npm test` (vitest)\n\n### References\n\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-parallel-execution.md#Story 16.5]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Decision 7 — Verify Flag Propagation]\n- [Source: src/lib/evaluator.ts — buildEvaluatorPrompt(), runBlindEvaluator()]\n- [Source: src/lib/workflow-engine.ts — propagateVerifyFlags(), dispatchTaskWithResult()]\n- [Source: src/modules/verify/orchestrator.ts — checkPreconditions()]\n- [Source: src/lib/coverage/evaluator.ts — evaluateCoverage(), updateCoverageState()]\n- [Source: src/lib/coverage/runner.ts — runCoverage(), checkOnlyCoverage()]\n- [Source: src/lib/agents/types.ts — OutputContract, TestResults interfaces]\n- [Source: src/lib/agents/output-contract.ts — buildPromptWithContractContext()]\n\n### Previous Story (16-4) Intelligence\n\n- Flag propagation implemented in `workflow-engine.ts` via `propagateVerifyFlags()` — called after every `dispatchTaskWithResult()` return.\n- Guards on `taskName === 'implement'` and `contract?.testResults` being non-null.\n- Reads harness state via `readStateWithBody()`, sets `session_flags.tests_passed` and `session_flags.coverage_met`, writes back.\n- 8 unit tests added. All 4747 tests pass.\n- `checkPreconditions()` in verify orchestrator already reads these exact flags — no changes needed to preconditions.\n- Code review caught: duplicate type definitions, missing `projectDir` parameter, misleading JSDoc. Be precise.\n- Currently `outputContract.testResults` is always `null` (hardcoded in engine). Flag propagation will activate when engine gains test result parsing from agent output.\n\n### Git Intelligence\n\nRecent commits:\n- `21e441c feat: story 16-4 — verify flag propagation`\n- `1831a88 feat: story 16-3 — telemetry writer module`\n- `07e94a2 feat: story 16-2 — engine-handled null tasks`\n- `e3c4761 feat: story 16-1 — hierarchical flow schema & parser`\n- Commit pattern: `feat: story {N}-{M} — {title}`\n\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n## Verification Requirements\n\n- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/16-5-coverage-deduplication-proof.md)\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n\n## Documentation Requirements\n\n- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/16-5-coverage-deduplication.md\n\n## Testing Requirements\n\n- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n\n## Dev Agent Record\n\n### Agent Model Used\n\n{{agent_model_name_version}}\n\n### Debug Log References\n\n### Completion Notes List\n\n### File List\n","numLines":189,"startLine":1,"totalLines":189}}}
