{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0149WCCWhrLmYu4mkMTd7zHs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017ipFH5TGzmN5RKw7brQg6Y","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-5-coverage-deduplication.md","old_string":"- [ ] Task 1: Add coverage deduplication to the evaluator prompt builder (AC: #1, #6)\n  - [ ] Modify `buildEvaluatorPrompt()` in `src/lib/evaluator.ts` (or the workflow engine's evaluator dispatch path) to accept optional coverage context\n  - [ ] When `coverage_met === true` in harness state and `testResults.coverage` exists in the output contract, append a coverage context block to the evaluator prompt\n  - [ ] Format: \"Coverage already verified by engine: {coverage}% (target: {target}%). No re-run needed.\"\n  - [ ] When no contract coverage data or `coverage_met === false`, do not append — evaluator uses normal flow\n\n- [ ] Task 2: Add coverage skip logic to the coverage command/runner path (AC: #2, #3, #4)\n  - [ ] In `src/commands/coverage.ts` or the coverage evaluation entry point, check harness state for `coverage_met === true` before running `runCoverage()`\n  - [ ] If `coverage_met` is already true, return a synthetic `CoverageResult` with data from the output contract (or simply skip the run and log the skip)\n  - [ ] If `coverage_met` is false or state is unavailable, fall through to existing `runCoverage()` path\n  - [ ] Ensure `checkOnlyCoverage()` respects the same skip logic\n\n- [ ] Task 3: Wire output contract data through the verify dispatch path (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4)\n  - [ ] The workflow engine already passes `previousOutputContract` to task dispatches via `buildPromptWithContractContext()` — verify that the verify task receives the implement task's output contract\n  - [ ] If the verify task does NOT currently receive the output contract, wire it through\n  - [ ] Extract `testResults.coverage` from the contract for use in deduplication decisions\n\n- [ ] Task 4: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#6)\n  - [ ] Test: evaluator prompt includes coverage context when `coverage_met === true` and contract has coverage\n  - [ ] Test: evaluator prompt does NOT include coverage context when `coverage_met === false`\n  - [ ] Test: evaluator prompt does NOT include coverage context when contract has `testResults: null`\n  - [ ] Test: `runCoverage` is not called when `coverage_met === true`\n  - [ ] Test: `runCoverage` IS called when `coverage_met === false` (fallback)\n  - [ ] Test: `checkPreconditions()` passes when both flags are true (existing test, verify still works)\n\n- [ ] Task 5: Verify backward compatibility (AC: #3, #4)\n  - [ ] Confirm that workflows without output contracts (older workflows) still run coverage normally\n  - [ ] Confirm the `codeharness coverage` CLI command works unchanged (it doesn't go through engine flag propagation)","new_string":"- [x] Task 1: Add coverage deduplication to the evaluator prompt builder (AC: #1, #6)\n  - [x] Modify `buildEvaluatorPrompt()` in `src/lib/evaluator.ts` (or the workflow engine's evaluator dispatch path) to accept optional coverage context\n  - [x] When `coverage_met === true` in harness state and `testResults.coverage` exists in the output contract, append a coverage context block to the evaluator prompt\n  - [x] Format: \"Coverage already verified by engine: {coverage}% (target: {target}%). No re-run needed.\"\n  - [x] When no contract coverage data or `coverage_met === false`, do not append — evaluator uses normal flow\n\n- [x] Task 2: Add coverage skip logic to the coverage command/runner path (AC: #2, #3, #4)\n  - [x] In `src/commands/coverage.ts` or the coverage evaluation entry point, check harness state for `coverage_met === true` before running `runCoverage()`\n  - [x] If `coverage_met` is already true, return a synthetic `CoverageResult` with data from the output contract (or simply skip the run and log the skip)\n  - [x] If `coverage_met` is false or state is unavailable, fall through to existing `runCoverage()` path\n  - [x] Ensure `checkOnlyCoverage()` respects the same skip logic\n\n- [x] Task 3: Wire output contract data through the verify dispatch path (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4)\n  - [x] The workflow engine already passes `previousOutputContract` to task dispatches via `buildPromptWithContractContext()` — verify that the verify task receives the implement task's output contract\n  - [x] If the verify task does NOT currently receive the output contract, wire it through\n  - [x] Extract `testResults.coverage` from the contract for use in deduplication decisions\n\n- [x] Task 4: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#6)\n  - [x] Test: evaluator prompt includes coverage context when `coverage_met === true` and contract has coverage\n  - [x] Test: evaluator prompt does NOT include coverage context when `coverage_met === false`\n  - [x] Test: evaluator prompt does NOT include coverage context when contract has `testResults: null`\n  - [x] Test: `runCoverage` is not called when `coverage_met === true`\n  - [x] Test: `runCoverage` IS called when `coverage_met === false` (fallback)\n  - [x] Test: `checkPreconditions()` passes when both flags are true (existing test, verify still works)\n\n- [x] Task 5: Verify backward compatibility (AC: #3, #4)\n  - [x] Confirm that workflows without output contracts (older workflows) still run coverage normally\n  - [x] Confirm the `codeharness coverage` CLI command works unchanged (it doesn't go through engine flag propagation)"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":526,"cache_read_input_tokens":99161,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":526,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":72,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Hody5ZigZ3cTL