{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Hody5ZigZ3cTLmGuBw8VE3","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story 16-5 implementation complete. Here's the summary:\n\n**What was done:**\n\n1. **`src/lib/evaluator.ts`** — Added `CoverageContext` interface and extended `buildEvaluatorPrompt()` (now exported) to accept optional coverage context. When coverage is pre-verified, the evaluator prompt includes \"Coverage already verified by engine: X% (target: Y%). No re-run needed.\"\n\n2. **`src/lib/coverage/runner.ts`** — Added optional `skipIfMet` parameter to both `runCoverage()` and `checkOnlyCoverage()`. When `skipIfMet=true` and `coverage_met=true` in harness state, returns a synthetic success result without executing coverage tools. Falls through to normal path when conditions aren't met.\n\n3. **`src/lib/workflow-engine.ts`** — Added `buildCoverageDeduplicationContext()` (exported for testing). Wired it into `dispatchTaskWithResult()` at step 7c — when the previous contract has coverage data and `coverage_met=true` in state, the coverage context string is appended to the dispatch prompt.\n\n4. **Tests** — 21 new tests across 3 files. All 4768 tests pass (up from 4747).\n\n5. **Backward compatibility** — CLI `codeharness coverage` command unchanged. All functions with new optional parameters work identically when called without them.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- The `dispatchTask` integration tests for prompt verification are weak — the mock setup makes it difficult to inspect the exact prompt the driver receives (the test checks `mockGetDriver().dispatch.mock?.calls` which may be undefined depending on mock chain). The tests pass but coverage of the actual prompt injection is more thoroughly tested via the unit tests on `buildCoverageDeduplicationContext`.\n- The `testResults` field is still always `null` in engine-built contracts (hardcoded). Coverage deduplication will only activate once the engine gains test result parsing from agent output (noted in story 16-4 as well). This is by design — the plumbing is ready.\n- The `skipIfMet` parameter on `runCoverage`/`checkOnlyCoverage` is not yet called from anywhere in production code. The engine-level deduplication happens via the prompt context (Task 3), not by calling `runCoverage(dir, true)`. The skip logic in the runner is available for future use (e.g., if a coverage evaluation entry point wants to skip).\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 29\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 16, Edit: 9, Grep: 4, Glob: 3, Skill: 1, Write: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx vitest run` specific tests (~80 lines), `npm test` full suite (~20 lines), `npm run build` (~10 lines)\n- Files read: 15 unique, 20 total reads (workflow-engine.ts read 4 times due to size limits)\n- Redundant operations: workflow-engine.ts required 4 reads due to file size exceeding the 10k token limit per read. No other redundancy."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ab1e1a398256da6e2 (use SendMessage with to: 'ab1e1a398256da6e2' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 103051\ntool_uses: 65\nduration_ms: 501950</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b6bb3bfc-8778-4f16-a616-88028acc2431","uuid":"0e805a72-d1f8-4368-8428-adca7033a2ba","timestamp":"2026-04-03T18:39:22.756Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-5-coverage-deduplication.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, test failures, unclear task specs, missing APIs)\n- Workarounds applied (anything hacky, copied patterns that felt wrong, TODOs left behind)\n- Code quality concerns (areas