on tests for prompt verification are weak — the mock setup makes it difficult to inspect the exact prompt the driver receives (the test checks `mockGetDriver().dispatch.mock?.calls` which may be undefined depending on mock chain). The tests pass but coverage of the actual prompt injection is more thoroughly tested via the unit tests on `buildCoverageDeduplicationContext`.\n- The `testResults` field is still always `null` in engine-built contracts (hardcoded). Coverage deduplication will only activate once the engine gains test result parsing from agent output (noted in story 16-4 as well). This is by design — the plumbing is ready.\n- The `skipIfMet` parameter on `runCoverage`/`checkOnlyCoverage` is not yet called from anywhere in production code. The engine-level deduplication happens via the prompt context (Task 3), not by calling `runCoverage(dir, true)`. The skip logic in the runner is available for future use (e.g., if a coverage evaluation entry point wants to skip).\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 29\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 16, Edit: 9, Grep: 4, Glob: 3, Skill: 1, Write: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx vitest run` specific tests (~80 lines), `npm test` full suite (~20 lines), `npm run build` (~10 lines)\n- Files read: 15 unique, 20 total reads (workflow-engine.ts read 4 times due to size limits)\n- Redundant operations: workflow-engine.ts required 4 reads due to file size exceeding the 10k token limit per read. No other redundancy."}],"totalDurationMs":501950,"totalTokens":103051,"totalToolUseCount":65,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":993,"cache_read_input_tokens":101300,"output_tokens":757,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":993},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
