{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01H2ZjB1WHRxR7cQsfdy3H45","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014Cjc1cYJQCoEjwdgUiy9Ku","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/16-5-coverage-deduplication-proof.md","content":"# Verification Proof: Story 16-5 — Coverage Deduplication\n\n**Story:** `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-5-coverage-deduplication.md`\n**Tier:** test-provable\n**Date:** 2026-04-03\n**Verifier:** Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n\n## Build & Test Summary\n\n| Check | Result | Detail |\n|-------|--------|--------|\n| Build (`npm run build`) | PASS | tsup compiled successfully, no errors |\n| Unit Tests (`npm run test:unit`) | PASS | 4768/4768 passed, 0 failed |\n| Lint (`npm run lint`) | WARN | 1 error (pre-existing), 53 warnings (pre-existing, none in story files) |\n| Coverage (`npm run test:coverage`) | PASS | 96.6% statements, 88.33% branches, 98.25% functions, 97.23% lines |\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Verification\n\n### AC#1: Evaluator prompt includes coverage context when `coverage_met=true` and contract has coverage\n**Result:** PASS\n\n- **File exists:** `src/lib/evaluator.ts` — `CoverageContext` interface exported (line 16), `buildEvaluatorPrompt(coverageContext?: CoverageContext)` exported (line 81)\n- **Function:** `formatCoverageContextMessage()` returns `\"Coverage already verified by engine: {coverage}% (target: {target}%). No re-run needed.\"` (line 66-68)\n- **Engine wiring:** `buildCoverageDeduplicationContext()` in `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` (line 117) reads `session_flags.coverage_met` from state, extracts `testResults.coverage` from contract, returns formatted context string\n- **Prompt injection:** `dispatchTaskWithResult()` appends coverage dedup context to prompt (lines 528-534)\n- **Test:** `evaluator.test.ts` > `AC#1,#6: includes coverage context when coverageContext is provided` — PASS\n- **Test:** `workflow-engine.test.ts` > `AC#1: returns coverage context string when coverage_met is true and contract has coverage` — PASS\n- **Test:** `workflow-engine.test.ts` > `AC#1,#6: appends coverage context to prompt when coverage_met is true` — PASS\n\n### AC#2: `runCoverage`/`checkOnlyCoverage` NOT invoked when `coverage_met=true`\n**Result:** PASS\n\n- **Skip logic:** `checkSkipIfMet()` in `src/lib/coverage/runner.ts` (line 200) returns synthetic `CoverageResult` when `skipIfMet=true` and `state.session_flags.coverage_met=true`\n- **Applied to both:** `runCoverage(dir?, skipIfMet?)` (line 220) and `checkOnlyCoverage(dir?, skipIfMet?)` (line 286)\n- **Test:** `runner.test.ts` > `runCoverage skipIfMet (story 16-5) > AC#2: skips coverage run when skipIfMet=true and coverage_met=true in state` — PASS\n- **Test:** `runner.test.ts` > `checkOnlyCoverage skipIfMet (story 16-5) > AC#2: skips coverage check when skipIfMet=true and coverage_met=true in state` — PASS\n- **Test:** `evaluator.test.ts` > `AC#2: does NOT include coverage context when coverageContext is undefined` — PASS\n- **Test:** `workflow-engine.test.ts` > `AC#2: does NOT append coverage context when coverage_met is false` — PASS\n\n### AC#3: Fallback to normal coverage when `testResults: null`\n**Result:** PASS\n\n- **Logic:** `buildCoverageDeduplicationContext()` returns `null` when contract is null or `testResults` is null (lines 127-130 in workflow-engine.ts)\n- **Runner:** `checkSkipIfMet()` returns null when `skipIfMet` is false, falling through to normal `runCoverage()` path\n- **Test:** `workflow-engine.test.ts` > `AC#3: returns null when contract has testResults: null` — PASS\n- **Test:** `workflow-engine.test.ts` > `AC#3: returns null when contract is null` — PASS\n- **Test:** `runner.test.ts` > `AC#3: does NOT skip when skipIfMet=false even if coverage_met=true` — PASS\n\n### AC#4: Coverage runs normally when `coverage_met=false` even with valid contract coverage\n**Result:** PASS\n\n- **Logic:** `buildCoverageDeduplicationContext()` checks `state.session_flags.coverage_met` first — returns null when false (line 130)\n- **Test:** `workflow-engine.test.ts` > `AC#4: returns null when coverage_met is false even with valid contract coverage` — PASS\n- **Test:** `runner.test.ts` > `runCoverage skipIfMet (story 16-5) > AC#4: does NOT skip when skipIfMet=true but coverage_met=false` — PASS\n- **Test:** `runner.test.ts` > `checkOnlyCoverage skipIfMet (story 16-5) > AC#4: does NOT skip when skipIfMet=true but coverage_met=false` — PASS\n\n### AC#5: `checkPreconditions()` passes when both flags are true without triggering coverage\n**Result:** PASS\n\n- **Function:** `checkPreconditions()` in `src/modules/verify/orchestrator.ts` (line 28) reads `tests_passed` and `coverage_met` from state — returns `{ passed: true }` when both true\n- **No coverage invocation:** `checkPreconditions()` only reads flags, does not call `runCoverage()` or `checkOnlyCoverage()`\n- **Test:** `verify.test.ts` > `checkPreconditions > passes when both flags are true` (line 76) — PASS\n- **Test:** `verify.test.ts` > `returns failure when coverage_met is false` (line 90) — PASS\n\n### AC#6: Evaluator can determine coverage from prompt context alone\n**Result:** PASS\n\n- **Format:** `formatCoverageContextMessage()` produces a self-contained string: `\"Coverage already verified by engine: 95% (target: 90%). No re-run needed.\"`\n- **Prompt inclusion:** The evaluator prompt includes this message when coverage is met, providing all needed data (actual coverage, target, pass status)\n- **Test:** `evaluator.test.ts` > `AC#1,#6: includes coverage context when coverageContext is provided` — PASS\n- **Test:** `workflow-engine.test.ts` > `AC#1,#6: appends coverage context to prompt when coverage_met is true` — PASS\n\n## Story 16-5 Test Inventory (21 tests, all PASS)\n\n### `src/lib/__tests__/evaluator.test.ts` — buildEvaluatorPrompt (story 16-5)\n1. AC#1,#6: includes coverage context when coverageContext is provided\n2. AC#2: does NOT include coverage context when coverageContext is undefined\n3. AC#3: does NOT include coverage context when no argument passed\n4. includes correct coverage and target values in context\n\n### `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` — buildCoverageDeduplicationContext (story 16-5)\n5. AC#1: returns coverage context string when coverage_met is true and contract has coverage\n6. AC#2: returns null when coverage_met is false\n7. AC#3: returns null when contract has testResults: null\n8. AC#3: returns null when contract is null\n9. AC#4: returns null when coverage_met is false even with valid contract coverage\n10. returns null when testResults.coverage is null\n11. gracefully returns null when state is unreadable\n12. uses default target of 90 when state.coverage.target is null\n\n### `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` — coverage deduplication in dispatchTask (story 16-5)\n13. AC#1,#6: appends coverage context to prompt when coverage_met is true\n14. AC#2: does NOT append coverage context when coverage_met is false\n\n### `src/lib/coverage/__tests__/runner.test.ts` — runCoverage skipIfMet (story 16-5)\n15. AC#2: skips coverage run when skipIfMet=true and coverage_met=true in state\n16. AC#4: does NOT skip when skipIfMet=true but coverage_met=false\n17. AC#3: does NOT skip when skipIfMet=false even if coverage_met=true\n18. falls through to normal run when state file is unreadable\n\n### `src/lib/coverage/__tests__/runner.test.ts` — checkOnlyCoverage skipIfMet (story 16-5)\n19. AC#2: skips coverage check when skipIfMet=true and coverage_met=true in state\n20. AC#4: does NOT skip when skipIfMet=true but coverage_met=false\n21. backward compat: works normally without skipIfMet parameter\n\n## Files Modified\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `src/lib/evaluator.ts` | `CoverageContext` interface, `formatCoverageContextMessage()`, extended `buildEvaluatorPrompt()` |\n| `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` | `buildCoverageDeduplicationContext()`, coverage dedup wiring in `dispatchTaskWithResult()` |\n| `src/lib/coverage/runner.ts` | `skipIfMet` parameter on `runCoverage()` and `checkOnlyCoverage()`, `checkSkipIfMet()` helper |\n| `src/lib/__tests__/evaluator.test.ts` | 4 new tests |\n| `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` | 10 new tests |\n| `src/lib/coverage/__tests__/runner.test.ts` | 7 new tests |\n\n## Final Result\n\n**ALL_PASS (6/6 ACs)**\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1025,"cache_read_input_tokens":34824,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1025,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01FfjRKMpZjLqLweCUGcGa6V","session_id":"b6bb3bfc-8778-4f16-a616-88028acc2431","uuid":"69a71d24-1594-48b2-a365-399cdec31fdf"}
